Find the remainder when $$33818^2 + 33819^2 + 33820^2 + 33821^2 + 33822^2$$is divided by 17.
inference:
$$33818^2 \equiv 12^2 \equiv 8^2 \equiv (-3)^2 \equiv 9 \pmod{17}$$

$$33819^2 \equiv 13^2 \equiv (-4)^2 \equiv 16 \equiv -1 \pmod{17}$$

$$33820^2 \equiv 14^2 \equiv (-3)^2 \equiv 9 \pmod{17}$$

$$33821^2 \equiv 15^2 \equiv 1 \pmod{17}$$

$$33822^2 \equiv 16^2 \equiv (-1)^2 \equiv 1 \pmod{17}$$

Adding these remainders,
$$9-1+9+1+1 \equiv 19 \equiv \boxed{2} \pmod{17}$$

Final Answer: \boxed{2}. I hope it is correct.
